{"id":14881564,"mediaExerciseId":"464db263-0fbd-4fdb-9b1c-0f1c336ec734","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"16","chapterTitle":"Financial Leverage and Capital Structure Policy","groupId":612418,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":570,"solutions":[{"id":5999007,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"First, we have to find out the earnings before interest and taxes which we denote with $EB$, where the current market value of equity $CM$ is $16,300,000$ and the cost of capita $C$ is $8.4\\%$\n\n$$\\begin{align*} EB&=CM \\times C\\\\[7pt] &=16,300,000 \\times 8.4\\%\\\\[7pt] &=16,300,000 \\times 0.084\\\\[7pt] &=1,369,200 \\end{align*}$$\nâ€‹\n \n\nSo, the earnings before interest and taxes is $\\boxed{\\$1,369,200}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Second, we have to find out the current earnings before interest and taxes which we denote with $CEB$, where the  earnings before interest and taxes $EB$ is $\\$1,369,200$ and the tax rate $TR$ is $22\\%$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nCEB&=\\frac{EB}{1-TR}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{1,369,200}{1-22\\%}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{1,369,200}{1-0.22}\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{1,369,200}{0.78}\\\\[12pt]\n&=1,755,384.615\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nSo, the current earnings before interest and taxes is $\\boxed{\\$1,755,384.615}$\n\nTherefore, because the corporation will have no debt, the weighted average cost of capital would be the same as $\\boxed{8.4\\%}$.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"f22bf50b-c02f-4dd4-832d-70d3c530586c","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.clou